Corona Avenue (formerly Union Avenue, also known as Alstyne Avenue) north side, between 92nd and 93rd Streets, showing in 4 views the Ludlow farmhouse erected about 1780 on Commons Tract. John R. Ludlow married Catalina Ditmars. Other owners were W. Card 1860; Isaac C. Card later, and Samuel Lord in 1873. The house was in ruins on June 28, 1930 and was razed by Oct. 1930.

Corona Avenue, north side, between 92nd and 93rd Streets, showing in 4 views the Ludlow house. In the back of the house is a 4 story factory occupying block No. 933. View No. 4, shows in the far background the steeple of St. Bartholomews Roman Catholic Church located between Judge and Ithaca Streets, north of Forty-third Avenue. See other views.
